{"author":{"id":"c52cb19fb02c210e51792121b2bae318d19fa8efb308ae796946bf1f79891ad1"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1784516712,"nonce":"0c3rYCRVb+HiwrVxZBJyWB78teQ=","title":"PG materialized views: model indexes + storage, and reader invertibility (Phase 3 PR 7)","message":"Follow-up to acb1c6d Phase 3 PR 6 (PostgreSQL materialized views, merged 45a4474 / PR #116). PR 6 models a matview's body only (a materialized flag on ViewModel) and delivers the publish-then-introspect-then-replan-empty contract for a scalar squealy-authored matview. It REFUSES a matview that carries anything a drop-and-recreate would silently reset. This follow-up (PR 7, the maintainer's split) turns those refusals into round-tripping support.\n\n1. MATVIEW INDEXES. squealy does not model indexes on a materialized view. Because a matview change re-creates it (there is no CREATE OR REPLACE MATERIALIZED VIEW), an out-of-band index would be silently dropped, so introspection currently REJECTS an indexed matview. PR 7: model indexes on a matview and diff them INCREMENTALLY (a CREATE INDEX add is Safe; recreating the matview to add an index would be wrongly blocked by the default policy since a matview DropView is Destructive) via new matview-index plan steps, so an indexed matview round-trips instead of being rejected. This is the reason the maintainer split PR 6 (body) from PR 7 (indexes).\n\n2. MATVIEW STORAGE / STATS. Introspection also rejects a matview carrying storage or planner-statistics settings a recreate would reset: relation storage parameters (reloptions) and TOAST storage parameters (on reltoastrelid), a tablespace or table access method that differs from the effective session default, and per-column SET STORAGE / SET COMPRESSION / SET STATISTICS / SET (n_distinct=...). PR 7 (or a sibling): model these so they round-trip rather than being refused.\n\n3. READER INVERTIBILITY (forward-authoring). render_create_view now emits CREATE MATERIALIZED VIEW ... WITH DATA, but Reader::read_create_view rejects the MATERIALIZED keyword (and the parser rejects the trailing WITH DATA). read_create_view returns a body-only ViewBody and is used by SQLite introspection (no matviews) and one PG offline-render test, NOT the live PG matview path (which uses relkind + read_view_query, verified working). So it is a reader-invertibility / forward-authoring gap, not a live replan bug. PR 7 (or Track F forward-authoring): thread materialized through read_create_view and accept the exact generated form, adding it to the render-parse-render round-trip corpus.\n\nNOTE (maintainer): the package FORMAT_VERSION is not bumped when a new object field is added (it has been 1 since the original DDL PRs, and enums/sequences/domains/exclusions/matviews all added KDL fields at v1). Deferred as out of scope because there are no cross-version package consumers yet.","files":null}]}